entries.context: Rico introduces the Circus show
entries.sourceEnglish: Welcome one and all to THE BIG CITY CIRCUS!
Where entertainment meets exotic animals... exotic animals meet art...
...and art meets...
FIRE!
Boy-oh-boy do we have a show for you TONIGHT!
Will it be participatory?
Yes!
Will it be dangerous?
Yes!
Will there be an intermission?
Not on your LIFE!
But we are selling popcorn in the lobby!
The acts you'll see tonight will each be more visually spectacular, more death-defying, more baffling than the last!
Performing for you is a cast of exotic animals who were BORN for the stage.
They want, NAY, they LIVE to entertain you!
They're HUNGRY for your applause!
HELL, their jobs depend on it!
And speaking of jobs, none of us would be here tonight if it weren't for our sponsor...
Mecha City's most benevolent benefactor, Mme. Derriere!
Let's give her a round of applause!
ALSO! I have a very big announcement at the end of tonight's show...
So stay tuned!
Our FIRST ACT comes to you from the grassy plains of the Savannah!
Please give a big round of applause for...

entries.context:
The Player gains control of the Elephant.
After the mini-game, the dialogue jumps to either line 35 or 47.
entries.sourceEnglish: ...ELI THE AFRICAN ELEPHANT!

entries.context: This dialogue is said if the Elephant tries to the go the wrong way
entries.sourceEnglish: This isn't the way to the stage...

entries.context:
After the Elephant's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Elephant gave a BAD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: Give a polite round of applause for Eli the Elephant who...
...tried their best to roll with it, but didn't quite fill the stage.
That elephant seemed kind of small...

entries.context: Formerly: That's what you get when you pay your performers peanuts!
entries.sourceEnglish: What do you expect when your performer only wants to be paid peanuts?
But seriously folks, these animals have traveled a long way to get here.
They've been rehearsing non-stop for months to bring you a great show...so be KIND.
It's tough being the one in the spotlight.

entries.context:
The Elephant goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a BAD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: What kind of lead-in was that?!
Even after all that rehearsing, the audience sure knows how to make you feel small.
Ha! Let me show you how it's done...
Once the crowd sees my routine, the Ringmaster is sure to announce a World Tour!

entries.context: Player gains control of the Gorilla.
entries.sourceEnglish: Don't keep them waiting!

entries.context:
After the Elephant's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Elephant gave a GOOD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: Wow—what a COLOSSAL feat!
A JUMBO serving of entertainment!
That was one helluva SHOW.
Am I RIGHT?!
You're RIGHT!
These animals have traveled a long way to get here.
They've been rehearsing non-stop for months—and it shows!
They deserve to be in the spotlight.
And so do I!

entries.context:
The Elephant goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a GOOD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: Tonight's crowd is easy!
It's thanks to all the rehearsing we've been doing.
Once the crowd sees my routine, the Ringmaster is sure to announce a World Tour!

entries.context: Player gains control of the Gorilla.
entries.sourceEnglish: Don't keep them waiting!

entries.context: Elephant repeater.
entries.sourceEnglish: Now is not the time to get stage fright!

entries.context: Back on stage: Rico introduces the Gorilla
entries.sourceEnglish: Alright... enough monkeying around...
Let's bring out the next act!
You'll be astounded at how intelligent she is.
Her DNA is 95% HUMAN and 5% MAGIC... and she takes direction like a champ!
From deep in the misty rainforests of the Congo—
Give me two opposable thumbs up for...

entries.context:
The Player gains control of the Gorilla again.
After the mini-game, the dialogue jumps to either line 68 or 81.
entries.sourceEnglish: QUEENIE THE GORILLA!

entries.context:
After the Gorilla's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Gorilla gave a BAD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: Okay, okay, sometimes live acts can get a little hairy.
Not everyone has the ape-titude to be a star!
I want my money back!
No refunds! You won't be getting your silver back!
Then we're leaving!
Don't leave! I guarantee our next few acts will be more bearable!
...and I'm not lyin' about the big finale!

entries.context:
The Gorilla goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a BAD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: What HAPPENED out there?!
The stupid audience just doesn't appreciate my talents!
Were there any presenters in the audience?
You know, for THE TOUR?
New plan!

entries.context: Player gains control of the Zebra.
entries.sourceEnglish: Just get out there and dazzle them!

entries.context:
After the Gorilla's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Gorilla gave a GOOD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: What APE-TITUDE under such HAIRY circumstances!
QUEENIE is a star!
What am I, chopped liver?
But it's true, these animals are something special.
...and they make me look good!
You hear that?! They LOVED YOU!
You can say that again!
Do you think there were any presenters in the audience?
I think so!
There were two Humans in the front row with dark hats who couldn't take their eyes off me!

entries.context: Player gains control of the Zebra.
entries.sourceEnglish: Ha ha! Good luck following my act!

entries.context: Gorilla repeater.
entries.sourceEnglish: We need that applause!

entries.context: Back on stage: Rico introduces the Zebra.
entries.sourceEnglish: This next act is a majestic beast from the Far East.
Let there be no Kung-Fu-sion, no one balances skill and speed quite like him!

entries.context:
The Player gains control of the Zebra again.
After the mini-game, the dialogue jumps to either line 95 or 113.
entries.sourceEnglish: Welcome to the stage YINYANG THE CHINESE ZEBRA!!

entries.context:
After the Zebra's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Zebra gave a BAD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: *Oof*
We weren't in balance today...
But sometimes, disasters turn out to be blessings!
We're confused!
Come on folks! That's the risk of live performance: you never know what will happen...
... and it could have been worse!

entries.context:
The Gorilla goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a BAD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: Some of my paint RUBBED OFF!
Are you joking?!
Did you forget that keeping up this act means keeping ourselves employed?
Finding another job with no Machines isn't going to be easy.
The Humans would like us JUST THE SAME if we performed as ourselves.
Ha! Not a chance!
Our job is to create magic and illusion, not authenticity!
Is it problematic that Kick is appropriating a Zebra's stripes? Isn't it a little bit rac—?
—Does it look like there's a real Zebra around here anywhere?
No.

entries.context: Jump to either line 113 or x (skipping Bear).
entries.sourceEnglish: And if there was, Kick Ass wouldn't have a role in the ensemble.

entries.context:
Branch (BAD Performance Version): 
If Sad left the Farm, Sad Ass enters.
entries.sourceEnglish: ...I'm not sure real Bears ride bicycles though...

entries.context: Player gains control of the Bear.
entries.sourceEnglish: Ha! Of course they do! Now get out there!

entries.context:
After the Zebra's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Zebra gave a GOOD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: What a RUSH! What a HIGH!
You saw it here tonight folks!
We're blurring the lines between theatre, dance, and circus!
We are INTERDISCIPLINARY!

entries.context: Player gains control of the Zebra.
entries.sourceEnglish: ...and it only gets better!

entries.context:
The Zebra goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a GOOD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: Your duet with the Ringmaster brought tears to my eyes!
WE NAILED IT!
Oooooo I can't wait to go on tour! Bigger crowds, cushier dressing rooms...
—and better costumes!
This paint is making me so DAMN ITCHY!
And I'm outgrowing my Elephant suit...
Then stop eating so much!
Keeping up this act means keeping ourselves employed!
We have it good here!
Finding another job with no Machines isn't going to be easy.
You're right—this is the BEST job—we've EVER had!

entries.context: Jump to either line 133 or x (skipping Bear).
entries.sourceEnglish: We've finally found a place to work where we all fit in.

entries.context:
Branch (Good Performance Version): 
If Sad left the Farm, Sad Ass enters.
entries.sourceEnglish: Says all of you who don't have to ride a bicycle...
We believe IN YOU!

entries.context: Player gains control of the Bear.
entries.sourceEnglish: Go show the crowd your cool moves Sad!

entries.context: Zebra repeater.
entries.sourceEnglish: You can DO IT!

entries.context: Back on stage: Rico introduces the Bear.
entries.sourceEnglish: Our next performer is done with hibernating backstage and ready to spring into action!
All the way from the Russian Tundra, give a globally warm welcome to my bike-riding Bolshevik—

entries.context:
The Player gains control of the Bear again.
After the mini-game, the dialogue jumps to either line s or d.
entries.sourceEnglish: CHEKHOV THE KAMCHATKA BROWN BEAR!

entries.context:
After the Bear's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Bear gave a BAD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: Let's take a moment to pause and reflect on that act before we shift gears...
Let me be real with you—the next animal is not what it seems...
It's even BETTER!
And after our next and final act, you'll get my big announcement!\n

entries.context:
The Bear goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a BAD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: Don't beat yourself up Sad, the bike was a late addition, you haven't had a lot of time to practice.
... I'm not made to ride a bike...
I don't want to derail the show, but it troubles me that I haven't found my talent yet...
... maybe tomorrow I can try the Seal act again...
You know Sad, you can't keep trying to be a different animal EVERY night.
Where the hell is Slow?!

entries.context: Jump to line x.
entries.sourceEnglish: It's time for the Finale!! If he screws this up for me, I'm going to—

entries.context:
After the Bear's section, Rico reviews the performance.
This is if the Bear gave a GOOD show.
entries.sourceEnglish: My head is spinning—with how great that act was!
I can barely hear you—give me another round of applause for CHEKHOV!
Even though every animal is different, under the spotlight they are all the same...
—STARS!
Bear with us folks! After the next and final act, you'll get my big announcement!

entries.context:
The Bear goes back stage.
This is the version of dialogue following a GOOD performance.
entries.sourceEnglish: Sad!! Your bike routine is OFF THE CHAIN!
Thanks... I've really got a handle on it now.
...you know, I'm really glad I came with you, Comrades...
Ha! 'Comrade'?
I think we're MORE than Comrades now!
We're closer than ever. We're an ENSEMBLE!
Is this what it feels like...

entries.context: Jump to line x.
entries.sourceEnglish: ...to be happy?

entries.context: Slow Ass arrives dressed as a Lion.
entries.sourceEnglish: Sorry I'm late.
This costume takes forever to p-p-put on...
*huff p-p-puff* I'm p-p-pouring sweat from the adrenaline already...
The Ringmaster can't afford to keep buying you new costumes before we go on Tour.
SO DON'T TOUCH THE FIRE!
*inhale*
*exhale*

entries.context: Jump to line x.
entries.sourceEnglish: Slow Ass! Get out there or I'll rip you a new one!

entries.context: If Bear was played, final line: Said to Slow Ass.
entries.sourceEnglish: Get your butt out there or I'll rip you a new one!!

entries.context: If Sad Ass is not present, a copy of the above dialog plays out.
entries.sourceEnglish: Sorry I'm late.
This costume takes forever to p-p-put on...
*huff p-p-puff* I'm p-p-pouring sweat from the adrenaline already...
The Ringmaster can't afford to keep buying you new costumes before we go on Tour.
SO DON'T TOUCH THE FIRE!
*inhale*
*exhale*

entries.context: Jump to line x.
entries.sourceEnglish: Slow Ass! Get out there or I'll rip you a new one!

entries.context: Back on stage: Rico introduces the Lion.
entries.sourceEnglish: Thanks for not staying home and watching TV.
A live performer and a live audience—
There's just no substitute for the energy of an
IN

entries.context: Needs space or hyphen at start
entries.sourceEnglish: -PERSON

entries.context: Needs space or hyphen at start
entries.sourceEnglish: -CROWD!
I hope you're all ready for the LAST and FINAL act of this evening.
There's nothing tame about it.
In fact, it's on...
FIRE!
All the way from India—my pride and joy:

entries.context:
The Player gains control of the Lion again.
After the mini-game, the dialogue jumps to either line s or d.
entries.sourceEnglish: BHUT JOLOKIA THE SPICY ASIATIC LION!

entries.context: After the Lion's section, Rico makes his big announcement!
entries.sourceEnglish: I'm not lyin' folks... that could have been better.
On the whole, I'd say tonight's show was a WILD success!
On the whole, I guess tonight was a bit off.
For those of you who have stayed—thank you for not walking out!
Let me hear you ROAR!
But don't worry!
Now it's time for my BIG ANNOUNCEMENT.
This hard-working cast of animals is being retired.
Tonight was their LAST SHOW.
Get ready for consistently perfect performances every night by the world's most exotic and endangered creatures!
Thanks to our new sponsor, the benevolent Mme. Derriere, we can finally afford our DREAM CAST...
of ROBOTS!
We're going to be the NOAH'S ARK of ENTERTAINMENT.

entries.context: The Player gains control of the Lion again.
entries.sourceEnglish: GOODNIGHT EVERYBODY!

entries.context: The Lion goes backstage to find the others.
entries.sourceEnglish: Hey everyb-b-body! Did you hear the announcement!?

entries.context: Rico is selling the donkeys to mysterious assknappers.
entries.sourceEnglish: Thanks for doing business folks!
{vpunch=100,0.75}UH OH! We're in huge trouble!
I've got a Plan! Slow Ass will save us...
@#$%&! We're doomed!
*whimper*
Where's the last donkey?
Right over there.
My show needs Robots more than donkeys in cheap costumes if I'm gonna get bums in seats.
No hard feelings, donkey.
Art dies when you stop innovating!
All right donkey. Get in the truck.
Wait... what if that sleazy Ringmaster is playing a trick on us?
What if this one is ACTUALLY a lion and it's going to eat us.
Then Rico can keep his animals AND our money.
I'll just never make it to the big stage with fakes.
Let's catch it quick, we're not being paid for overtime.

entries.context: Dialogue options. Jump to either line x or y.
entries.sourceEnglish: He's a circus hack, not an evil genius, you idiot.

entries.context: Dialogue option 1.1. Slow Ass runs and hides.
entries.sourceEnglish: Run
Where did it go?
*wheeze* Screw it. Let's leave it and take the others.
P-p-phew, they didn't find me!

entries.context: Jump to line x. Slow Ass exits.
entries.sourceEnglish: Time to b-b-be b-b-brave...

entries.context: Dialogue option 1.2. Slow Ass does a convincing roar.
entries.sourceEnglish: Roar
EEEEE!!!! IT IS A LION!!!
I'm outta here!!
I've b-b-been p-p-practicing!
I'm the only one left—I've got to rescue the others!

entries.context: Jump to line x. Slow Ass exits.
entries.sourceEnglish: Time to b-b-be b-b-brave and rescue the others.

entries.context: The camera moves over to Mme. Derriere and Grandma Kulan, who is just on her way out.
entries.sourceEnglish: Mme. Derriere, may I have moment of your time?
Oh my! Really?
My dear, the deaths of your precious grandson and those poor helpless villagers who burned alive—it breaks my heart.
All that matters is that we don't look back.
But his life was cut short during the tragic fires of Bumpkin Village exactly 6 months and 3 weeks ago.
My darling Joey would have loved this show.
With all your power and resources, will you prevent explosions like Bumpkin's from ever happening again?
I can promise you that the research I'm funding right now will transform the face of the world.
They deserved Progress!
They deserved purposeful jobs!
Bumpkinites deserved more than dangerously out-of-date and accident-prone equipment.
Walk with me.
But I don't even have the strength to go back and visit Bumpkin...

entries.context: End of Circus.
entries.sourceEnglish: And even you can play a part in it!

entries.sourceEnglish: 6 months later

entries.context: Zookeeper Rose speaks to the Slow Ass.
entries.sourceEnglish: Your poor swollen joints are looking so much better.
As long as we keep using this Ointment for your arthritis, you should be able to keep up with the others.

entries.context: Rose blows whistle and the other donkeys enter.
entries.sourceEnglish: Now let's get to work!

entries.context: Rose speaks to the group of Asses.
entries.sourceEnglish: Oh Good Morning my beautiful Asses!
I'm so glad you're all here, because I have an important announcement!
The Zoo's Board of Directors wants me to choose an Ass to be the face of a new advertising campaign.
They know that Asses sell tickets!
So I've made up a game to decide who it will be.
I call it ASS OF THE WEEK.
Every day, you'll compete to see who can capture the attention of the most visitors by giving them what they came here to see.

entries.context: Big = Hulk (Can be renamed for more culturally appropriate name)
entries.sourceEnglish: Will it be you The Hulk?

entries.context: Kick = Littlefoot (Can be renamed for more culturally appropriate name)
entries.sourceEnglish: Is it you Littlefoot?

entries.context: Sad = Eeyore (Can be renamed for more culturally appropriate name)
entries.sourceEnglish: Or maybe, you, Eeyore?

entries.context: Smart = Sophie (Can be renamed for more culturally appropriate name)
entries.sourceEnglish: Or Sophie?

entries.context: Slow = Achilles
entries.sourceEnglish: Or, Achilles? Now that your joints aren't swollen anymore!
We'll add up your scores at the end of the week, to find out who wins.

entries.context: Rose exits.
entries.sourceEnglish: I'll go open the gate and then we'll get started.

entries.context: This dialogue is said if Sad Ass is present.
entries.sourceEnglish: *sigh*
I've got a Plan!
ONE, I'm going to run into the pen.
TWO, I'm going to capture the attention of the visiting Humans.
THREE, I'm going to have the highest score.
AND WIN ASS OF THE WEEK!
Easy.
Have fun fighting over second place suckers!

entries.context: Rose returns.
entries.sourceEnglish: Get ready to meet the visitors.
Those TOURISTS with the colourful Hawaiian shirts love it when you turn Left and Right to give them a good look at you.
THE TEACHERS with clip boards like it when you demonstrate a classic donkey Kick!\n
Those lab-coat wearing RESEARCHERS are fascinated with animal behaviour, so show them a Dust Bath!
And of course that OLD LADY who is always here just wants to be Listened to.
You got that memorized, right?
Attention spans aren't what they used to be!

entries.context: The other Asses run off.
entries.sourceEnglish: So you have to be quick to catch the visitors before they get bored.

entries.context: Zookeeper Rose addresses Slow Ass.
entries.sourceEnglish: Oh, Achilles!
I want you to have an equal chance of winning.

entries.context: The Player is given control of Slow Ass. Mini-game begins.
entries.sourceEnglish: If you need any extra Ointment for your joints to keep up with the others, just come find me.

entries.context: Read on the Info Sign of the Zoo.
entries.sourceEnglish:
Fun facts about Equus Asinus: 

- Originally from Africa
- Can live into their 50s
- Are extremely nimble on rocky terrain
- Used as working animals for at least 7,000 years
- Don't like being in the rain

entries.context: Said by Zookeeper Rose when the Player presses 'x' near her and your Ointment bar is empty.
entries.sourceEnglish: Get your Ointment!

entries.context: Said by Zookeeper Rose when the Player presses 'x' near her and the Ointment bar is NOT empty.
entries.sourceEnglish: Your joints look good!

entries.context: Said by Grandma Kulan when the Player presses 'x' close to her.
entries.sourceEnglish: Sigh... Joey would have loved this...

entries.sourceEnglish: I'm b-b-beat... time for b-b-bed...
TUESDAY

entries.context: Beginning of the next day.
entries.sourceEnglish: GOOOODDDD MORNING ASSSSSSES!
Superb work yesterday!

entries.context: Jump to line 13, 14, 15, 16, or 17.
entries.sourceEnglish: The current leader is...

entries.context: Dialogue 1.1. If SMART Ass is winning
entries.sourceEnglish: Sophie! Everyone can tell how smart she is!

entries.context: Dialogue 1.2. If BIG Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: The Hulk! Who doesn't love a big donkey?

entries.context: Dialogue 1.3. If KICK Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Littlefoot, you are kick-starting the race for Ass of the Week!

entries.context: Dialogue 1.4. If SAD Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Eeyore! Everyone wants to cheer you on!

entries.context: Dialogue 1.5. If SLOW Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Achilles! That ointment is really making a difference!

entries.context: Dialogue options (1.1-1.5) converge.
entries.sourceEnglish: The crowd is arriving and it'll be just as busy as yesterday!
You know what to do...
TOURISTS love it when you turn Left and Right to give them a good look at you.
TEACHERS like it when you do a donkey Kick!
RESEARCHERS want to see a Dust Bath!

entries.context: Jump to line 24, 26, or 28.
entries.sourceEnglish: And of course that OLD LADY who is always here just wants to be Listened to.

entries.context: Dialogue 2.1. If SMART is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: @#$%&! These Humans ALL LOOK THE SAME!

entries.context: Mini-game begins.
entries.sourceEnglish: Out of the way, my adoring fans are waiting!

entries.context: Dialogue 2.2. If SLOW is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: @#$%&!—Slow Ass?!—it's gotta be that magic OINTMENT!

entries.context: Mini-game begins.
entries.sourceEnglish: Ha! Without that ointment, you're nothing Slow Ass.

entries.context: Dialogue 2.3. If SMART is not winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Someone is cheating. I know it!
We can't b-b-be good at everything, Smar—

entries.context: Mini-game begins.
entries.sourceEnglish: Keep your mouth shut, Slow Ass!

entries.context: Said by Slow Ass upon exiting the map at the end of Day 2, after the mini-game.
entries.sourceEnglish: P-p-phew! I'm p-p-parched!
WEDNESDAY

entries.context: Beginning of the next day.
entries.sourceEnglish: GOOOODDDD MORNING ASSSSSSES!

entries.context: In MIRO: 'Who's in the lead?' // Jump to line 35, 36, 37, 38, or 39.
entries.sourceEnglish: The current leader is...

entries.context: Dialogue 3.1. If SMART Ass is winning
entries.sourceEnglish: Sophie, your guts and guile make you a star!

entries.context: Dialogue 3.2. If BIG Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: The Hulk has a massive advantage!

entries.context: Dialogue 3.3. If KICK Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Littlefoot, people are hooked on you!

entries.context: Dialogue 3.4. If SAD Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Eeyore, even YOU have to smile at how well you're doing.

entries.context: Dialogue 3.5. If SLOW Ass is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Achilles, keep up the hard work!

entries.context: Dialogue options (3.1-3.5) converge.
entries.sourceEnglish: Wowzer! There's a long line outside the main gates.
I met some SUPER FRIENDLY PEOPLE who told me they LOVE it when donkeys Lie Down and look cute.

entries.context: Jump to line 42, 46, or 48.
entries.sourceEnglish: Now get out there and show those Visitors how adorable you can be.

entries.context: Dialogue 4.1. If SMART is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: STOP STEPPING on my hoofs out there Big Ass!
You're holding me BACK!
It's not my fault your score is so low.

entries.context: Jump to line 52 or 53.
entries.sourceEnglish: Ha! It's both your faults that you suck!

entries.context: Dialogue 4.2. If SLOW is winning.
entries.sourceEnglish: Don't get full of yourself Slow. Your luck is about to run out!
